Package com.ibm.streams.operator.samples.operators

Class MaxMinOperator

java.lang.Object
com.ibm.streams.operator.AbstractOperator
com.ibm.streams.operator.samples.operators.MaxMinOperator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Operator
@PrimitiveOperator(description="Simple sample operator that monitors the incoming tuples and sends the max or min value that is seen on the attribute specified by the monitoredAttr parameter on the first output port along with the original tuple on the second output port.") @InputPorts(@InputPortSet(cardinality=1)) @OutputPorts(@OutputPortSet(cardinality=2)) public class MaxMinOperator extends AbstractOperator
Sample operator that demonstrates the usage of CustomLiteral and Attribute parameters.

The operator supports 2 parameters:
monitorType: One of 'Max' or 'Min' custom literal to indicate whether the operator is keeping track of max or min values.
monitoredAttr: The attribute on the input schema to monitor for max or min values. The attribute must be an int32.

The operator processes incoming tuples and keeps track of max/min values (as specified by the monitorType parameter) of the input schema attribute specified by the monitordAttr parameter. The current max/min value is returned as a tuple on the first output port. The original tuples are also passed through on the second output port.
